Import Data and Peak tables from xslx

Source: R/import_dataXL.R
import_dataXL.Rd

import_dataXL() reads sheets from xslx and load them.

Usage

import_dataXL(xlsx_file_name, sheet_name, interactive_output = FALSE)

Arguments

xlsx_file_name

A name of excel file.

sheet_name

A name of indicating the sheet of interest.

interactive_output

Boolean indicating whether to output the table in interactive mode using reactable.

Value

The table of the tibble format or as a reactable if interactive_output is TRUE.

Examples

library(MDAW)
excel_file <- "Gastric_NMR.xlsx"
path <- system.file("extdata", "Gastric_NMR.xlsx", package = "MDAW")
MDAW::import_dataXL(xlsx_file_name = path,
    sheet_name = "data")
